NAME
	topic_client_subscribe - register a process to receive messages published in a topic.

SYNOPSIS
	#include <topic.h>

	int topic_client_subscribe(topicid_t id)

DESCRIPTION
	topic_client_subscribe() allows a process to declare itself a subscriber to a topic in order to retrieve future messages. If the specified topic doesn't exist, it returns an error.

RETURN VALUE
	On success, zero is returned. Otherwise, a value of -1 is returned, and the global variable errno is set to indicate the error.

ERRORS
	If the specified topic doesn't exist, ENOENT is returned.
	If the user is already registered in this topic, EALREADY is returned.
	Not enough memory to create a new publisher. [ENOMEM]
